Project: workapi
Language: go
Description: A production-grade, STANDARD-LIBRARY-ONLY Go backend that adds two real concerns on top of a clean-architecture task API: BEARER-TOKEN AUTH on mutating routes, and an asynchronous BACKGROUND WORKER that processes events emitted when a task is created, with GRACEFUL DRAIN on shutdown. No external dependencies: net/http Go 1.22 ServeMux, log/slog, context, encoding/json, sync, sync/atomic. Clean layering, dependencies point inward only: handlers -> service interface -> store interface, and service -> an event-enqueuer interface the worker satisfies. Multi-package layout (cmd/ + internal/{config,models,store,worker,auth,service,api}). Cross-package symbols are used by importing the package and qualifying (models.Task, store.Store, service.TaskService, store.ErrNotFound, worker.Worker, auth.TokenAuth). Only exported names cross package boundaries.
Go module path: guildlm.dev/workapi

TARGET_FILE: cmd/server/main.go
Purpose of this file: package main — composition root. Import config, store, worker, service, api, context, log/slog, net/http, os, os/signal, time. main(): logger := slog.New(slog.NewJSONHandler(os.Stdout, nil)); cfg := config.Load(); if err := cfg.Validate(); err != nil log and os.Exit(1); s := store.NewMemStore(); w := worker.NewWorker(cfg.QueueSize, logger); w.Start(); svc := service.NewTaskService(s, w) (the worker satisfies service.EventEnqueuer); handler := api.NewRouter(svc, cfg.AuthToken, logger); build *http.Server{Addr: cfg.Addr, Handler: handler, ReadTimeout, WriteTimeout}; run ListenAndServe in a goroutine; graceful shutdown on os.Interrupt via signal.NotifyContext — on signal, srv.Shutdown(a context.WithTimeout of cfg.ShutdownTimeout) to stop accepting requests, THEN w.Stop() to drain the worker. Log lifecycle with slog. Imports context, log/slog, net/http, os, os/signal, time, and the config/store/worker/service/api packages.

All files in this project:
